# Force LF in the working tree for every text file. Without this, Git for
# Windows with core.autocrlf=true rewrites checkouts to CRLF, which breaks:
#   - bash scripts (`set -euo pipefail\r` is an unknown option)
#   - Biome / Prettier / dotnet format CI gates (file content differs)
#   - Dockerfiles and other tooling read from inside Linux containers
# Setting `text=auto eol=lf` makes Git store and check out LF everywhere,
# independent of the contributor's autocrlf setting.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary file types — never normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tgz binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.otf binary
*.dll binary
*.exe binary
*.pdb binary
*.nupkg binary
*.snk binary
